## The Hidden Costs

### 1. MTU-Based Scaling

Dreamdata's pricing scales with monthly tracked users (MTUs). As your traffic grows, so does your bill — even if you're on the same tier. The $750/mo starting price is exactly that: a starting price. High-traffic B2B sites can see costs climb significantly.

### 2. Custom Attribution Requires the Top Tier

If you need custom attribution models — defining your own rules for how credit is assigned to touchpoints — you need Attribution Advanced (custom pricing). On Activation Starter, you get 6 pre-built models but no customization. This is a meaningful limitation for teams with complex B2B sales motions.

### 3. Implementation Time

Dreamdata's setup takes 4-8 weeks for CRM integration, data pipeline configuration, and historical data processing. That's not a direct cost, but it's a real cost — engineering time, delayed time-to-value, and the opportunity cost of waiting.

### 4. BigQuery Access Is Gated

If you want to query your attribution data directly in BigQuery, that requires Attribution Advanced tier. On lower tiers, you work within Dreamdata's UI.

