## 5 Alternatives With Transparent Pricing

If Dreamdata's pricing doesn't fit, here are alternatives across different budget ranges. We've included actual prices where published and estimates where not.

### Pricing Comparison Table

| Platform | Free Tier | Entry Paid | Mid-Tier | Enterprise | Best For |
|----------|-----------|------------|----------|------------|----------|
| **HockeyStack** | No | ~$1,399/mo | ~$2,200/mo | Custom | All-in-one B2B |
| **mbuzz** | Yes | $29/mo | $99/mo | $299/mo | Model flexibility |
| **Factors.ai** | Check | $399/mo | Custom | Custom | Affordable B2B |
| **Bizible** | No | Enterprise | Enterprise | Enterprise | Salesforce-native |
| **GA4** | Yes (free) | N/A | N/A | N/A | Free basics |

*Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product. We've included it as one option among several.*

### 1. HockeyStack — All-in-One B2B ($1,399-2,200/mo)

HockeyStack bundles attribution, web analytics, and surveys into one platform. No published pricing — reports suggest GTM Intelligence starts around $1,399/mo and GTM Execution around $2,200/mo.

**Why consider over Dreamdata:** Faster deployment (~2 weeks vs 4-8), bundled analytics, LinkedIn impression tracking. More expensive but more comprehensive.

**Why stick with Dreamdata:** Dreamdata's free tier, transparent pricing, and journey visualization are stronger. HockeyStack costs 2-3x more.

Read more: [HockeyStack Alternatives](/articles/hockeystack-alternatives)

### 2. mbuzz — Model Flexibility at $29-299/mo

mbuzz offers 7 attribution models plus custom rules via a rule editor, with server-side tracking through native SDKs. Setup takes minutes, not weeks. *Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product.*

| mbuzz Tier | Price | Records |
|------------|-------|---------|
| Free | $0 | <%= free_event_limit_display %> |
| Starter | $29/mo | 1M |
| Growth | $99/mo | 5M |
| Pro | $299/mo | 25M |

**Why consider over Dreamdata:** 3-25x cheaper on paid tiers. Custom attribution rules on all plans (including free). 10-minute setup vs 4-8 weeks.

**Why stick with Dreamdata:** Dreamdata's journey visualization and LinkedIn audience activation are features mbuzz doesn't match. If visual journey mapping matters most, Dreamdata is the better tool.

Read more: [mbuzz vs Dreamdata](/articles/mbuzz-vs-dreamdata)

### 3. Factors.ai — Affordable B2B ($399/mo)

Factors.ai offers AI-powered B2B attribution starting at $399/mo — roughly half Dreamdata's Activation Starter price. Includes account identification, multi-touch attribution, and path analysis.

**Why consider over Dreamdata:** ~47% cheaper entry point, AI-powered insights, faster setup (2-4 weeks).

**Why stick with Dreamdata:** Dreamdata's journey visualization is deeper. Factors.ai is newer with a smaller community. Dreamdata's free tier lets you evaluate before committing.

### 4. Bizible (Adobe Marketo Measure) — Enterprise Salesforce

Bizible is the enterprise standard for Salesforce-native B2B attribution. Custom pricing only — typically enterprise contracts.

**Why consider over Dreamdata:** Deepest native Salesforce integration. Built for enterprise ABM motions. Stronger governance and compliance features.

**Why stick with Dreamdata:** Dreamdata is far more affordable, faster to set up, and better suited for mid-market B2B. Bizible's 3-6 month implementation and enterprise pricing make it overkill for most teams.

### 5. GA4 — Free But Limited

Google Analytics 4 is free and includes basic attribution. It's not a Dreamdata replacement — but it's a starting point if you're not ready for paid attribution tools.

**Why consider over Dreamdata:** Free. Fast to set up. Good enough for basic channel-level attribution.

**Why stick with Dreamdata:** GA4 has no B2B features — no company identification, no account-based attribution, no CRM integration, no pipeline analytics. It's a web analytics tool, not a B2B attribution platform.

Read more: [GA4 Attribution Alternatives](/articles/ga4-attribution-alternatives)

